273,"dateUpdated":276,"description":348,"excerpt":276,"extension":277,"headline":296,"meta":349,"navigation":279,"path":350,"seo":351,"socialImage":352,"stem":353,"tags":354,"__hash__":358},"blog/blog/watmap.md","WATMAP and other delights",{"type":10,"value":298,"toc":346},[299,303,310,325,334,337],[30,300,302],{"id":301},"we-can-rebuild-it-for-you-wholesale","We can rebuild it for you wholesale!",[13,304,305],{},[306,307],"img",{"alt":308,"src":309},"My son reimagined via WATMAP","/media/watmap.00.png",[13,311,312,313,318,319,324],{},"Processing2/3 code written by ",[17,314,317],{"href":315,"rel":316},"https://github.com/tsulej/GenerateMe/tree/master/watmap",[21],"GenerateMe",". See their ",[17,320,323],{"href":321,"rel":322},"https://generateme.tumblr.com/",[21],"TumblrBlog"," for use and tips.",[13,326,327,328,333],{},"A ",[17,329,332],{"href":330,"rel":331},"http://everythingability.com/",[21],"friend"," thinks of it a \"a poor-man's GAN\". I can see the similarities: an image is \"recreated\", using elements from something else.",[13,335,336],{},"Original developer refers to it as part of a \"glitch-aesthetic\" which I get - but it's not a glitch, an error. There are seeming \"hiccups\" in the discontinuities. It's essentially a tile-mosaic replicator using a quad-tree to focus on sizes. It takes a long time to process, mainly due to the quad-tree preocessing.",[13,338,339,340,345],{},"I thought that ",[17,341,344],{"href":342,"rel":343},"https://www.instagram.com/richard.winters/",[21],"Richard Winters"," (last time I checked, all images had been removed, which makes me sad) was using a custom version inspired by WATMAP, but I've long-since changed my mind. Using square-subsections (instead of variadic-sized rectangles) and processes each color channel (RGB?) separately. So, channel-based tile-sets.",{"title":269,"searchDepth":270,"depth":270,"links":347},[],"A glitch-aesthetic mosaic image-remaker built in Processing by somebody else",{},"/blog/watmap",{"titl